issue.title: bench: WalletMigration benchmark broken
issue.body:
master @ cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462
```bash
export CC=clang
export CXX=clang++
cmake -B build -DBUILD_BENCH=ON
cmake --build build
./build/bin/bench_bitcoin -filter=WalletMigration
bench_bitcoin: wallet/wallet.cpp:1772: void wallet::CWallet::InitWalletFlags(uint64_t): Assertion `m_wallet_flags == 0' failed.
Aborted (core dumped)
```

events.body: I think I got it, will create a PR soon.

Looks like this is a "low" benchmark, but it would be good to run those at least once in the CI. Maybe in the asan task? Otherwise, issues like this could be missed.

I guess this is also the reason why corecheck is down?

Ref https://corecheck.dev/bitcoin/bitcoin/pulls/32273

cc @m3dwards

I think they should just be run in any task that runs the benchmarks (i.e drop the usage of -priority-level). Otherwise, if benchmarks are so slow that they can't be run "normally" (or under a single iteration, which was introduced so that benchmarks could be run in the CI iirc), they should probably just be deleted; especially if nobody is even going to run them, when changing related code.

Incomplete observations from debugging:

One part of the problem is that [`HasLegacyRecords()`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/walletdb.cpp#L549-L570) is returning false for some reason in the migration benchmark case, that's why [`success` is true when it shouldn't be](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/wallet.cpp#L4538-L4543).

The wallet is not blank, migration has not been performed, but `success == true`, so it does seem right to crash here.

-------

The wallet migration benchmark creates a "legacy" wallet using SQLite since #31241, maybe this has something to do with why `HasLegacyRecords()` isn't working as intended.

> One part of the problem is that [`HasLegacyRecords()`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/walletdb.cpp#L549-L570) is returning false for some reason in the migration benchmark case, that's why [`success` is true when it shouldn't be](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/wallet.cpp#L4538-L4543).

The problem is that the scripts and keys created are not being saved/ written into the DB (mocked/ in memory), so if those objs are persisted the test and `HasLegacyRecords` work both fine. I'll create the PR asap.

> > One part of the problem is that [`HasLegacyRecords()`](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/walletdb.cpp#L549-L570) is returning false for some reason in the migration benchmark case, that's why [`success` is true when it shouldn't be](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/cdc32994feadf3f15df3cfac5baae36b4b011462/src/wallet/wallet.cpp#L4538-L4543).
> 
> The problem is that the scripts and keys created are not being saved/ written into the DB (mocked/ in memory), so if those objs are persisted the test and `HasLegacyRecords` work both fine. I'll create the PR asap.
